  "comments": [
    {
      "id": "01KVN7K3QC5M16RPDQYF0Z1HSS",
      "body": "architecturally, I dont want LurMotorn to default into thinking of one of the peer to peer agents to be a host that holds the source of truth. I would rather think of each agent to own the truth of the items most interesting and relevant for them to interact with. for instance in chess it might make sense for each agent to \"host\" the pieces of their own team, since those are the pieces the player will interact with - so interaction is snappy and tight. in a multiplayer game about shooting down the other players units it might make sense for each agent to own/host the spawning of its own units but the movement of the oponents units after they are spawned - so that it feels responsive to spawn and accurate to aim and shoot at the oponents miving units.",
      "created_at": "2026-06-21T13:58:15.532Z",
      "resolved": false,
      "author_kind": "human",
      "author_name": "johan",
